# entities
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.placements.name.normal=Arena Option
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.switchIDs=A comma-separated list of switch IDs assigned to this arena.\n\nIf more than one arena is assigned to one switch,\npressing it will pick a random arena to start.
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.arenaArea=The SID of the arena map. (optional)\n\nThe SID of the map is its path relative to the Maps/ folder,\nexcluding order and side markers. For example, if my map is in\n"Maps/SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/1-LazureLake.bin",\nits SID is "SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/LazureLake".\n\nIf empty, defaults to the current map's SID.\n\nNOTE: Madhunt lets you specify the side of the arena map\nby putting a hash and the side at the end of the SID\n(like "SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/LazureLake#B"),\nbut this is bugged since 2.4.5 and does not work.
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.spawnLevel=The name of the arena room.
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.spawnIndex=The spawn index Hiders and Seekers should use when teleporting.\n\nIf positive, this spawn index is used directly.\nIf negative, each player picks a random index between\n0 (inclusive) and the given value (exclusive).
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.initialSeekers=How many seekers should the game be started with.
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.tagMode=TODO
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.goldenMode=TODO
entities.Madhunt/ArenaOption.attributes.description.hideNames=TODO

