entities.Madhunt/TransitionBooster.placements.name.normal=Transition Booster
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBooster.attributes.description.targetDir=The direction the booster should go towards.
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBooster.attributes.description.targetArea=The SID of the map the player should be teleported to.\n\nThe SID of the map is its path relative to the Maps/ folder,\nexcluding order and side markers. For example, if my map is in\n"Maps/SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/1-LazureLake.bin",\nits SID is "SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/LazureLake".\n\nIf empty, defaults to the current map's SID.\n\nNOTE: Madhunt lets you specify the side of the target map\nby putting a hash and the side at the end of the SID\n(like "SnipUndercover/MadhuntMaps/LazureLake#B"),\nbut this is bugged since 2.4.5 and does not work.
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBooster.attributes.description.targetLevel=The name of the room the player should be teleported to.
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBooster.attributes.description.targetID=The ID of a Transition Booster Target that the player should arrive from.

entities.Madhunt/TransitionBoosterTarget.placements.name.normal=Transition Booster Target
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBoosterTarget.attributes.description.targetID=The ID of this Transition Booster Target.
entities.Madhunt/TransitionBoosterTarget.attributes.description.boosterDir=The direction the booster should arrive from after being teleported.

